SP  - 101
EP  - 108
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
AB  - This paper presents time-series forecasts for end-use categories for U.S. merchandise exports. Both the basic principles of end-use accounting and the fundamental methods of Box-Jenkins time-series techniques are explained. The result is a set of predicted values of U.S. merchandise exports which may be used to analyze and evaluate other export forecasting models.
